{
  "name": "Birthday Cake Crumbl Cookie",
  "description": "A Crumbl birthday-cake copycat that is really a chilled cream-cheese protein dip/frosting — cream cheese creamed with protein and sweetener, rainbow sprinkles folded through, no baked base. Same cream-cheese-frosting genre as the Protein Cream-Cheese Frosting sub-recipe (and its Cool-Whip sibling); eaten cold by the spoon or as a thick cookie. House calibration: 1 cup powdered sugar replaced with granulated Splenda (sweetness-matched); modeled with light cream cheese.",
